<TITLE> President, PM, opposition leader join devotees for Akheri Munajat </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Tongi, Jan 24 (bdnews24.com)  President Md Zillur Rahman, prime minister Sheikh Hasina and opposition leader Khaleda Zia attended the Akheri Munajat, or final prayers, of the three-day Biswa Ijtema on the outskirts of Dhaka from noon on Sunday. The president and prime minister reached the Ijtema ground at 11:20am while the opposition leader reached there at around 10:30am. Arrangements were also made for ministers, MPs and other VIPs, said Abul Bashar Mohammad Ameer Uddin, administrative officer of the Ijtema venue. The president joined the final prayers at the north-western side of the Ijtema ground, beside the prayer stage. The prime minister was seated on a special stage atop the Civil Aviation Authority building. Cabinet members and MPs were there with her. Opposition leader and BNP chairperson Khaleda Zia was offering her prayers at a designated area on the rooftop of Atlas Motors. Top party leaders accompanied her. Hundreds of thousands of devotees from Bangladesh and around the world joined the final prayers of the annual Ijtema, the largest Muslim congregation after the Hajj, held on the banks of the Turag river in Tongi, outside the capital. b
